subject: Cthulhu updates and name-dot parsimony

messageBody:
I pushed a pile of changes; they're all under the "June 16" heading on <https://github.com/adiabatic/qs-literature/commits/gh-pages>. Simply click on the ellipses to get the list of changes for that particular commit.

Incidentally, is there a consensus on how to name-dot organizations like "the American Archaeological Society" and its abbreviation "A. A. S."? I'm uncomfortable with anything less dotted than "·american ·archaeological ·society" and "·a. ·a. ·s", but Read prefers to play faster and looser with ending delimiters than I do…

I suppose I'm just worried that I might introduce a giant pile of ambiguity by not explicitly identifying the tail end of a proper noun. Writing names of people surnamed "Wood" might show how Read's parsimony might trip up a reader, but a fully illustrated example of "·bianca ·wood" vs. "·bianca wood" vs. "·bianca would" isn't coming to me at this hour.

Thoughts?
